the general idea for the remote was that it should be easy to use , attractive and electricity saving .
people might lose it a lot and it could be sold by using a slogan .
for the technical aspect , the remote should have a chip with an interface that controls it , infrared bulbs , battery , wires , buttons and holder .
there should be extra features such as timer , lid buttons , on-off button , channel lock and display clock .
the remote could be in different shapes , preferably compact and t-shaped .
the material should be of non-allergic nature .
the different systems that exist were infrared and radio-waves .
